  "jayman-built": "---\ntitle: \"Jayman Built Review\"\nbuilder: jayman-built\nrating: 2\naddress:\n  city: Calgary\n  province: AB\n  postal: \"\"\npros:\n  - \"Initial marketing materials and Fit and Finish Brochure were detailed and appealing.\"\ncons:\n  - \"Misleading brochure advertising — 80\\\"/10mil shower specs not reflected in contract.\"\n  - \"Vague and ambiguous contract language ('other shower stalls applicable to plan').\"\n  - \"Post-signing spec changes: 70\\\"/5mil → 75\\\"/6mil, neither matching brochure.\"\n  - \"16-day delay from sales manager Michael Klassen with no initiated contact.\"\n  - \"Nearly $7,000 quoted to 'upgrade' to the specs already advertised in the brochure.\"\n  - \"Builder terminated the agreement rather than resolving the dispute.\"\nstatus: terminated\npossession_date: null\n---\n\nMy second attempt at purchasing a new home was with Jayman Built. The property was at **71 Legacy Reach Court SE** in the **Legacy** community, Calgary. The model was an **Avid 20 with revised ensuite**. My sales associate was **Brittney Mack**.\n\nI received the purchase agreement on **March 4, 2025**. Key line items: **$7,820** for the \"Revised Ensuite\" (4-piece ensuite with separate soaker tub and shower) and **$12,600** for \"Fit and Finish Extra (2).\"\n\nThe core dispute was over the ensuite shower. Jayman's [Fit and Finish Brochure](https://www.jayman.com/assets/Uploads/JAY-2609-Fit-and-Finish-Brochure-CAL_WEB_2025.pdf) described: *\"4-piece ensuites include curbless tiled shower recessed into the floor sloped towards a 32\" linear drain. Walls are tiled to ceiling. Includes 80\" height, chrome frame, 10 mil glass shower door.\"* The contract was vague, referencing only \"other shower stalls applicable to plan.\"\n\nPost-signing, **Brittney Mack** initially stated the spec would be 70\"/5mil glass (April 10), revised to 75\"/6mil (April 11) — neither matching the brochure. Jayman quoted nearly $7,000 to \"upgrade\" to the advertised specs. Escalation to sales manager **Michael Klassen** was requested on April 11 but met with 16 days of silence.\n\nOn **April 28, 2025**, I sent a formal dispute to **Stephanie Myers** (VP, Single Family), CC'd to **David Hooge** (COO) and **Jay Westman** (Chairman & CEO), citing *contra proferentem* and requesting the brochure specs plus written confirmation of the **Navien NPE 240A tankless water heater**.\n\nJayman Built terminated the agreement in early May 2025.\n\n### Key Events\n\n*   **Property:** 71 Legacy Reach Court SE, Calgary (Legacy community)\n*   **Model:** Avid 20 with revised ensuite\n*   **Sales Associate:** Brittney Mack\n*   **Sales Manager:** Michael Klassen (mKlassen@jayman.com)\n*   **VP:** Stephanie Myers (smyers@jayman.com)\n*   **Agreement:** March 4, 2025 ($7,820 Revised Ensuite + $12,600 Fit and Finish Extra)\n*   **Brochure URL:** https://www.jayman.com/assets/Uploads/JAY-2609-Fit-and-Finish-Brochure-CAL_WEB_2025.pdf\n*   **Dispute Filed:** April 28, 2025\n*   **Outcome:** Terminated by Jayman Built, early May 2025\n",
  "sterling-homes": "---\ntitle: \"Sterling Homes Review\"\nbuilder: sterling-homes\nrating: 4\naddress:\n  street: \"37 Quarry Park Blvd SE\"\n  city: Airdrie\n  province: AB\n  postal: T4A 3R1\npros:\n  - \"Transparent and collaborative sales process with Jason Tang.\"\n  - \"Comprehensive purchase agreement — all schedules present, warranty included.\"\n  - \"More affordable than the Jayman property, with key features (full-height tile, front garage).\"\n  - \"Quick-possession timeline — moved in before Jayman broke ground or Douglas would have completed.\"\n  - \"Thorough warranty team (Aly Derwent, Adam Pocock, Deborah Curran, Brendan McElroy, Nick Mintchev).\"\n  - \"Good seasonal work — driveway, grading, landscaping.\"\ncons:\n  - \"Dismissive and unprofessional site supervisor (Mike), according to Colton's post-possession notes — foam off-gassing safety concern on possession day.\"\n  - \"Buggy Virtuo app — critical Android/Pixel UI bug, unresponsive agents.\"\n  - \"Eavestrough issues unresolved for weeks (June 30 → July 11 Empire Envelope 'fix' → ongoing).\"\n  - \"Hot water failure in December 2025, still under investigation.\"\n  - \"Outsourced customer service for some warranty issues.\"\nstatus: success\npossession_date: \"2025-06-02\"\n---\n\nMy experience with Sterling Homes was the third and final chapter in my home-buying journey. The property is at **Langley Terrace SE, Airdrie, AB T4A 3R1** — the **\"Luna\" model**, job number **J#158004**. It was a **quick-possession home**.\n\n## Sales & Pre-Possession\n\nMy first contact was **Jason Tang** (lanark@sterlingcalgary.com). The difference from my previous two builder experiences was immediate — no sales pressure, straight answers. The purchase agreement was comprehensive and clear, with every schedule present and the home warranty included. I worked with two lenders (ATB and CIBC); my CIBC mortgage advisor was **Heather Hannah**. Mortgage approval came on **May 21, 2025**.\n\nThe home inspection was conducted on **May 28, 2025** by **Marty Keough** of **Nook & Cranny Home Inspections**. The report came back clean — minor cosmetic issues only.\n\nI took possession on **June 2, 2025**.\n\n## Post-Possession & Warranty\n\nThe warranty team has been the primary interface for post-possession issues:\n\n| Person | Role |\n|---|---|\n| **Aly Derwent** | Customer Response Lead (warranty@sterlingcalgary.com) |\n| **Adam Pocock** | Customer Relations Coordinator |\n| **Deborah Curran** | Warranty Response Representative |\n| **Brendan McElroy** | Warranty Technical Lead |\n| **Nick Mintchev** | Warranty Tech |\n\nSterling uses the **Virtuo** app for warranty communication, which has a critical UI bug on Google Pixel phones (task nav hidden under Android buttons) and generally unresponsive agents.\n\n## Open & Resolved Warranty Items\n- Eavestrough (Jun 30 → Jul 11 → ongoing) — **Jaspreet Gill** (warranty contact), **Don Allary** / Empire Envelope\n- Stairwell window cracked — replacement July 15, 2025\n- Driveway/walkway poured — July 24, 2025\n- Fireplace missing crystals / not turning on — Enercare appointment August 7, 2025\n- Ceiling texture repair (kitchen) — August 18–21, 2025\n- Hot water failure — late December 2025, Lynx Plumbing to attend year-end inspection\n- Batten paint, parging, front sod, front steps, seasonal topsoil, soffit, hallway texture — various pending items\n\n**Year-End Inspection:** May 26, 2026 (Nick Mintchev + Lynx Plumbing)\n**Warranty Expiry:** June 2, 2026\n\n### Key Events\n\n*   **Property:** Langley Terrace SE, Airdrie AB T4A 3R1\n*   **Model:** Luna (quick-possession)\n*   **Job Number:** J#158004\n*   **Sales Contact:** Jason Tang (lanark@sterlingcalgary.com)\n*   **Mortgage:** CIBC, Heather Hannah — approved May 21, 2025\n*   **Home Inspection:** May 28, 2025 — Marty Keough, Nook & Cranny Home Inspections\n*   **Possession:** June 2, 2025\n*   **Warranty Expiry:** June 2, 2026\n*   **Year-End Inspection:** May 26, 2026\n",
